The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Prattville had a population of 24. The population density was {{convert|39.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Prattville was 22 (92%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (4%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], and 1 (4%) from two or more races. No residents were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Prattville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0658618 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

There were 8 households, and the average household size was 3.0. The median age was 66.8{{nbsp}}years.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 101 housing units at an average density of {{convert|167.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 8 (8%) were occupied year round and 86 (85%) were used seasonally.<ref name=DP1/>

At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median household income was $70,313 and the median family income  was $71,250. Males had a median income of $71,250 versus $36,250 for females. The per capita income for the CDP was $37,786. None of the population and none of the families were below the [[poverty line]].<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

